                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-250-off1469 t18320405-250-crimeloc1471"></join>. I saw the prisoner and another <rs id="t18320405-250-deflabel1472" type="occupation">boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-250-defend2127 t18320405-250-deflabel1472"></join> pass his door on the 28th of March, and the prisoner took a hat from the door; I called Stop thief! and pursued: some gentleman tried to stop him - he threw down the hat, and a gentleman brought it to me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-250-person2131">
                  WILLIAM 
                  STRAY
               <interp inst="t18320405-250-person2131" type="surname" value="STRAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-250-person2131" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-250-person2131" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I attend to the business of Mr. Samuel Gravenor. About eight o'clock in the evening I was informed there was a thief - I ran out, and saw the prisoner running with the hat - he threw it down; we ran on to Cabbage-court, where I lost sight of him for an instant, but a Policeman took him - I met him with him - I know he is the man.</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that he took<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183204050105"></xptr>the hat intending to purchase it, but being rather inebriated it fell from his hand. He received a good character.</p>
